  { Mobile phone

    { History of xG

      table { ll
        1973 ☰ First handheld cellular mobile phone
        1980s ☰ ~1G~: first generation of mobile telecommunications standards
        1991 ☰ ~2G~ - GSM (Global System for Mobile Communications) - followed by 2.5G, 2.75G and 2.875G
        2001 ☰ ~3G~ - UMTS (Universal Mobile Telecommunications System)
         ☰ ~4G~ - LTE (Long Term Advanced)
         ☰ ~5G~
      table }

    }
    { UICC - Universal integrated circuit card

      An *UICC* is a → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smart_card[smart card] (integrated circuit card) which is implemented in smart phones running on 2G, 3G, 4G and 5G networks.

    }
  }
